00:03:16.489 --> 00:03:18.510
## Where do you get your ideas?

00:03:18.510 --> 00:03:21.510
It's been my experience that creative projects
are self-sustaining. The more you write, the

00:03:21.510 --> 00:03:24.950
more things you want to write about and the
more you program the more programming ideas

00:03:24.950 --> 00:03:25.510
you have.

00:03:25.510 --> 00:03:29.129
For me each video spawns more videos. The
daylight saving one, for example, originally

00:03:29.129 --> 00:03:33.269
contained spots for information about longitude
and time zones and the seasons that got cut

00:03:33.269 --> 00:03:35.530
but will probably become their own videos
at some point.

00:03:35.530 --> 00:03:40.390
Also, I listen to a monstrous number of audiobooks
and podcasts. If you're interested, you can

00:03:40.390 --> 00:03:43.790
see some of my favorites here. These help
me keep in touch with the wider world and

00:03:43.790 --> 00:03:47.400
expose me to ideas and information that I
would not have come across on my own.

