00:03:53.690 --> 00:03:56.260
## "What's the best way be successful on YouTube?"
Joe Kowalski, 44074

00:03:56.260 --> 00:03:57.930
Make videos people want to watch.

00:03:57.930 --> 00:04:01.440
I'm not trying to be glib here but when asked
this question I see many YouTubers talk about

00:04:01.440 --> 00:04:05.959
the importance of upload schedules and managing
your social media and colloborations, and

00:04:05.959 --> 00:04:08.430
my experience says that's completely backwards.

00:04:08.430 --> 00:04:12.129
If your videos aren't interesting, no one
will care that you upload them regularly.

00:04:12.129 --> 00:04:15.830
And twitter followers don't get you views,
views get you twitter followers and people

00:04:15.830 --> 00:04:17.380
who want to collaborate with you.

00:04:17.380 --> 00:04:20.900
I know it's not very helpful advice, but it's
the most truthful advice I can give.

